				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree - its rough - but then again - I have more fun soloing with my beastie than I do my shaman... wouldn't say easier but more fun.
<br />

<br />
Usuallly waiting till the last second to cast  my Shard/Spear spell at the endhelps (when I'm worried, I keep 2 memmed for a double whammy), and also - at least on Mith Marr - Crystline Silk Nets can be bought for less then 10pp at times - and are fairly easy to get from Crystal Caverns (they provide 2 charges of grasping roots for when the DD doesn't do it).
<br />

<br />
There's also a quest involveing Warrens and Stonebrunt that will give you a 5 charge snare - the quest is listed as Mirandas dice I think on Allaq's.
<br />

<br />
I've noticed this getting easier to deal with as I've advanced in levels - 53 and after - my pet stuns from behind quite a but.
<br />

<br />
Another option, though kinda expensive (ie - might not want  to use it unless  you're in a situation that you're really nervous about runners) is to give your pet a sereated bone dirk...has one of the necro darkness spells as a proc...on mith mar - seen then go for anywhere from 100-500p - other servers, I'm not sure...I keep one around when I see it going for
<br />
a respectable price for when I find myself in a dungeon enviroment alone or with a partner that can't snare.
<br />

