Earth pet = root
<br />

<br />
Thx~
<br />

<br />
Anyway... as for dilemma, I'll add off of what Niran said.
<br />

<br />
5. Pull to an area where you'll have plenty of time to KILL the mob, before it reaches reinforcements. (which coincides with #3 of Niran's post)
<br />

<br />
I used to complain about this as well, back when I was a noob, but Sony will do nothing to remedy this (in fear of making us unbalanced, i.e. overpowered). Suck it up and improvise.
<br />

<br />
As for going for a snare item for mobs that run, dont bother: 
<br />

<br />
1. When the items that contain the snare ability are depleted, you're screwed. (Refer to "5." above)
<br />
2. If your pet dies for some reason, due to adds or letting them tank for too long when you back out to heal, you're screwed. /bye SBD... (Refer to "5." above)
<br />

<br />
Hobble of Spirits, you might say.. well.. how about NO. I've tried aggro kiting in multiple zones with this skill, using Flash of Light and Sha's Revenge as my aggro. You're better off finding a cleric to heal your butt than attempt to do that. Takes too long, and too nerve wracking. 
<br />
Another thing with Hobble of Spirits, IF you have the skill, once it is cast on your warder, kiss Snow/Flame/Rellic goodbye for the duration. These spells cannot be recast OVER Hobble, hence killing your pets dps AND the slight stun effect on the proc for Hobble's spell duration (Unless you want to suspend or kill your pet, rebuff it, then go back to work.. but that seems like it wastes mana and time to me).
<br />

<br />
Anyway.. live by #5 and you'll be golden for all of your soloing years. Trust me, I've lived it... and still am. 
<br />

