				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A few suggestions:
<br />

<br />
1. Try a different class, you obviously don't have the patience to learn how to play this one effectively
<br />
2. Group with someone else who does have root
<br />
3. Once you've worked out how far a running mob will get before you've mashed it, learn to pull it back a bit further before getting stuck in - that way it won't make it back to it's buddies when it's on its last legs
<br />
4. SOW yourself up and bravely give chase ! (assuming you make it to level 30)
<br />
5. Go and visit some of the nicer 'train' zones like Unrest and see what chaos a runner in a confined space can do....finishing off a ghoul only to see his brother and 15 of his slightly bigger mates coming round the corner is priceless! Sure you might wipe, but hey, you might not <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />
It's moment's like that I remember about the game, not the 'Gosh that was really easy to kill because I have root' moments! 
<br />

<br />
Regards,
<br />
Blubs<br />_________________<br />'There is no spoon'</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
