			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is some hopefully helpful advice as I don't think Sony would give us snare. (you have to imagine every class is supposed to have their niche and this dosen't seem like the one for Beastlords.) this Coat tails off what many other people said but is a little different:
<br />

<br />
when you are fighting a mob with high HPs hopefully the only time you will run into a issue with something running a long distance. Every thing else should die quickly  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
at 25-30% life recast all of your Dots then as the mob hits 20-22% hit it with as many powerful nukes as you can. This is what I call the poor mans snare. By virtue of front loading your damage and ensuring the mob is doted their movement will have its biggest drop initially and hopefully they will be running mostly in the lower 10% of ther HPs meaning they are severly slowed due to being near death. This has proven useful to me many times when fighting white and yellow mobs. if you can get them from 20% to 15% or below quickly their movement is severly hampered. 
<br />

<br />
All things aside I can understand the wanting of the snare security blanket, but figuring out different ways of doing things is the fun of the game.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Kilwan Stormbeast
<br />
52 Beastlord of Bristlebane
<br />
Clan of the Roc
<br />

<br />
That which does not have the potential of killing you is often not worth doing.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
